{"updated_at": "2012-08-26T07:50:03Z", "repo": "rails", "created_at": "2012-08-26T07:50:03Z", "owner": "rails", "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/comments/8031069", "id": 8031069, "issue_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/6549", "issue_id": 6549, "user": {"repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/lexmag/repos", "type": "User", "html_url": "https://github.com/lexmag", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/lexmag/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/lexmag/subscriptions", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/lexmag/following{/other_user}", "gravatar_id": "5187030ec0cd68b5026199e9e4054dda", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/lexmag/orgs", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/lexmag", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/lexmag/gists{/gist_id}", "avatar_url": "https://0.gravatar.com/avatar/5187030ec0cd68b5026199e9e4054dda?d=https%3A%2F%2Fidenticons.github.com%2F26e8038468b101cc834b42122ecf8612.png", "id": 248290, "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/lexmag/events{/privacy}", "login": "lexmag", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/lexmag/received_events", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/lexmag/followers"}, "body": "If you use pry, you use it in all of yours projects.\nWhy do not simple create global `~/.pryrc`?\n\n    #!env ruby\n    if File.exist?(rails = File.join(Dir.getwd, 'config', 'environment.rb'))\n      require rails\n\n      require 'rails/console/app'\n      require 'rails/console/helpers'\n\n      if Rails.version =~ /^3.2/\n        extend Rails::ConsoleMethods\n      end\n    end\n\nAnd you\u2019ll have access to application models and console helpers.\n\n    ~/myapp% pry\n\nNo extra gems in Gemfile. You still can use `rails c`", "_id": {"$oid": "523806b2bd3543c15100c9a6"}, "html_url": "https://github.com/rails/rails/pull/6549#issuecomment-8031069"}
